    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR3j0195-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:01:05.842+09:00">Among the people there was one who made thievery his profession.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:01:49.186+09:00">He taught his son all about his craft.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:08:28.954+09:00">The son of the thief was proud of his own talent</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:06:44.696+09:00">and he considered himself superior to his father by far.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:09:54.203+09:00">the son of the thief would invariably enter first and leave last,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:09:42.849+09:00">Everytime they went thieving,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s7" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:10:28.07+09:00">he would leave aside the light (goods) and only take the heavy ones.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s9" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T17:47:46.699+09:00">his eyes were able to see in the dark</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s10" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T17:47:54.406+09:00">And he was praised by all the thieves.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s8" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T21:13:36.012+09:00">His ears were able to hear a long distance,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s11" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T23:51:14.121+09:00">He boasted, comparing himself with his father and said "I am not lacking in any way, compared to the old one's craft</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s12" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:25:31.478+09:00">and I do surpass him in hardness and strength.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.h1" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T19:44:58.976+09:00">On the Thief and His Son</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s15" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:42:21.74+09:00">The thief said: "It is not quite like this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s16" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:00:28.909+09:00">As for wise and thorough learning and abundant self-posession,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s17" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-02T23:59:13.489+09:00">you are not there yet".</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s13" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:27:52.09+09:00">If it goes on like this,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s14" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:27:19.324+09:00">what worry is there about my success."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s18" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:37:24.754+09:00">The son of the thief said: "In the principles of thievery</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s19" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:38:33+09:00">gaining valuables is considered success.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s20" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:39:14.003+09:00">As for me and the old one,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s21" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:39:57.594+09:00">my success is always greater than his.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s22" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:40:50.515+09:00">Now I am still young of years,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s23" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:41:21.689+09:00">but when I reach the old one's age,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s24" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:42:00.709+09:00">I will then have techniques of a totally different nature."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s25" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T00:42:45.461+09:00">The thief said: "It is not quite like this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s26" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T17:50:20.617+09:00">When using my craft,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s27" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T17:51:33.96+09:00">one can enter multi-layered walls,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s28" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T17:53:38.399+09:00">and one can find out hidden treasure hoards.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s29" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T17:55:29.403+09:00">But if there is but a single slip or error,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s30" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T17:56:45.077+09:00">disaster and woe will follow it.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s31" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T19:49:39.863+09:00">When no traces are left that can be followed,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s32" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T19:49:46.023+09:00">when one conforms to the changes in the situation and one cannot be trapped,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s34" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:04:55.371+09:00">You are not there yet."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s35" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:06:46.684+09:00">The son of the thief still did not heed this lesson</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s36" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:07:52.671+09:00">In the next night, the thief, together with his son, entered a wealthy house.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s37" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:08:33.768+09:00">He told his son to enter into the treasury.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s38" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:17:24.48+09:00">The thief's son was taking a huge ammount of valuable goods,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s39" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:17:10.308+09:00">when the thief shut the door and turned the key.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s40" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:18:12.122+09:00">The noise was heard by the master of the house</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s42" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T19:59:03.078+09:00">and saw that the lock was in place as it had been.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s44" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:19:49.193+09:00">The thief's son was inside the treasury,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s45" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:20:09.825+09:00">with no plan to get out.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s43" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T19:59:09.333+09:00">The master returned inside.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s46" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:21:36.846+09:00">Through scratching and crawling, he made the noise of mice biting and chewing.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s47" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:22:12.383+09:00">When the master heard that a mouse was inside the treasury damaging the goods,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s48" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:22:45.618+09:00">he could not avoid going out again.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s49" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:24:08.008+09:00">When he held up a lantern and opened the lock to have a look,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s50" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:24:23.303+09:00">the thief's son escaped and ran.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s51" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:25:14.203+09:00">The master's household all together chased him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s52" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:26:35.799+09:00">The thief's son was distressed,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s53" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:26:55.916+09:00">believing that he would not be able to escape</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s54" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:27:56.786+09:00">he ran, heading for the moat.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s55" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:28:19.732+09:00">He tossed a stone into the water,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s56" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:29:44.224+09:00">so that the chasers exclaimed that the thief had entered the water</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s57" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:30:37.222+09:00">and they guarded the fence, trying to find and catch (the thief).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s58" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:31:56.644+09:00">The thief's son was able to escape because of this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s59" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:34:29.009+09:00">He blamed his father, saying: "Even birds and beasts know how to care for their children</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s83" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T18:39:36.526+09:00">Now, thievery is a base and ugly craft,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s84" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:45:59.5+09:00">but it still takes ones own experience to be able to face the world.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s90" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:05:16.791+09:00">This is exactly like when the thief's son boasts before his father.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s105" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:48:14.819+09:00">Do not be confused!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s91" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:25:17.455+09:00">If one can do away with honour and live humbly,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s92" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:28:15.822+09:00">if one declines grandeur and follows what one loves in peacefulness and unimportance,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s93" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:30:39.06+09:00">in frugality and with ones mind focused on study,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s94" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:32:15.717+09:00">with ones heart-mind sunken deeply into the cosmic order;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s95" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:33:43.34+09:00">and if one is not moved by base customs,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s96" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:35:33.732+09:00">one can then be in harmony with other people</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s97" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:36:05.087+09:00">and can gain merits and fame.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s100" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T20:06:47.496+09:00">That is exactly how the thief's son gained wisdom through distress</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s101" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:44:18.216+09:00">and in the end became one who could stride the world on his own.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s102" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T19:44:49.346+09:00">You are also close to this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s103" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T21:47:22.182+09:00">You should not be afraid of a sudden pursuit by a calamity while you are in hiding (like the thief in the treasury).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s99" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T20:11:51.834+09:00">and everything will go well and orderly.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s98" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-03T20:11:23.233+09:00">One works or keeps to oneself, according to being in office or being in hiding,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s33" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T19:53:55.451+09:00">then this is something that can not be performed by someone who does not have first-hand experience.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s41" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T19:58:39.699+09:00">the household chased away the thief and then returned</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s62" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:02:03.828+09:00">The thief said: "From now on</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s63" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:02:58.479+09:00">you will now have to stride the world alone.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s64" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:07:05.986+09:00">As for all the skills of men,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s65" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:07:52.675+09:00">those that are learned from others</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s66" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:10:01.474+09:00">are only partially understood.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s67" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:11:01.617+09:00">Those that are learned by oneself</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s68" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:12:35.519+09:00">are inexhaustible in their application.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s71" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:16:22.559+09:00">My bringing you into distress</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s72" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:16:34.049+09:00">was to put you into safety.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s73" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:17:09.028+09:00">My trapping you</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s74" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:17:20.689+09:00">was to free you.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s75" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:18:50.808+09:00">Had their been no entering the treasury and the hardship of being chased,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s76" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:21:22.665+09:00">how would you have been able to come up with the ruses of chewing like a mouse and throwing a stone?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s77" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:22:26.568+09:00">It was because of the difficulties that you became wise</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s78" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:23:22.785+09:00">and facing disaster you came up with the ruses.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s79" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:39:47.677+09:00">Once the deeps of the heart-mind have opened</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s80" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:40:41.541+09:00">they will not again return to confusion.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s81" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:42:04.095+09:00">You indeed will have to stride the world alone now.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s82" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:45:21.513+09:00">In the end, he became a thief that was unmatched in the world.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s60" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:53:23.909+09:00">What have I, your son, done wrong</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s61" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T20:55:14.82+09:00">that you are mistreating me like this?"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s69" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T21:16:16.892+09:00">And moreover as for difficulties and distress, as for utter desolation,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s70" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T21:35:28.359+09:00">they are what strengthens a person's will and grows a person's benevolence.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s85" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T21:21:27.37+09:00">And moreover, as for the gentleman's attitude towards doctrine, virtue, merits, and fame.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s86" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T21:26:44.568+09:00">The descendants of officials, adorned with the correct hairstyle and with a hereditary salary,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s87" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T21:29:55.246+09:00">they do not know the beauty of benevolence and righteousness and the profits of scholarly learning.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s88" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2024-06-05T23:34:06.5+09:00">Those who already have fame and honour</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s89" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2024-06-05T23:36:07.558+09:00">can hardly be able to equal the heroes of the past and surpass the older exploits.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3j0195_wiki_001-3.s104" xml:lang="en" resp="#fsiegmund" modified="2023-08-04T21:46:41.046+09:00">Think of what you have gained yourself in your hear-mind and it will be good.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
